Note:
Runa Standard Library: Logging Core Module

Production-grade logging infrastructure providing structured, high-performance logging
with comprehensive handler support, filtering, and formatting capabilities.
:End Note

Import "datetime" as DateTime
Import "collections" as Collections
Import "os" as OS

Note: Log levels in order of severity
Type LogLevel is:
    | TRACE
    | DEBUG
    | INFO
    | WARNING
    | ERROR
    | CRITICAL

Note: Core log record structure
Type called "LogRecord":
    timestamp as Float
    level as LogLevel
    logger_name as String
    message as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    thread_id as String
    process_id as String

Note: Logger configuration and state
Type called "Logger":
    name as String
    level as LogLevel
    handlers as List[Handler]
    filters as List[Filter]
    parent as Optional[String]
    propagate as Boolean
    enabled as Boolean

Note: Handler interface for log output
Type called "Handler":
    handler_type as String
    level as LogLevel
    formatter as Formatter
    enabled as Boolean

Note: Message formatting interface
Type called "Formatter":
    format_template as String
    include_timestamp as Boolean
    include_level as Boolean
    include_logger as Boolean

Note: Log filtering interface
Type called "Filter":
    filter_type as String
    criteria as Dictionary[String, Any]
    enabled as Boolean

Note: Global logger registry
Let logger_registry as Dictionary[String, Logger] = dictionary containing

Note: Current system time accessor
Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Import "time"
    Return time.get_current_timestamp

Note: System process ID accessor
Process called "get_process_id" returns String:
    Return OS.get_process_id

Note: System thread ID accessor Process called "get_thread_id" returns String:
    Return "main"

Note: Create formatted timestamp string
Process called "format_timestamp" that takes timestamp as Float returns String:
    Return DateTime.format_timestamp with timestamp as timestamp

Note: Convert log level to numeric value for comparison
Process called "level_to_numeric" that takes level as LogLevel returns Integer:
    Match level:
    When TRACE: Return 10
    When DEBUG: Return 20
    When INFO: Return 30
    When WARNING: Return 40
    When ERROR: Return 50
    When CRITICAL: Return 60

Note: Convert string to log level
Process called "string_to_level" that takes level_str as String returns LogLevel:
    Match level_str:
    When "TRACE": Return TRACE
    When "DEBUG": Return DEBUG
    When "INFO": Return INFO
    When "WARNING": Return WARNING
    When "ERROR": Return ERROR
    When "CRITICAL": Return CRITICAL
    Otherwise: Return INFO

Note: Convert log level to string
Process called "level_to_string" that takes level as LogLevel returns String:
    Match level:
    When TRACE: Return "TRACE"
    When DEBUG: Return "DEBUG"
    When INFO: Return "INFO"
    When WARNING: Return "WARNING"
    When ERROR: Return "ERROR"
    When CRITICAL: Return "CRITICAL"

Note: Check if logging level should be processed
Process called "should_log" that takes logger_level as LogLevel and message_level as LogLevel returns Boolean:
    Let logger_numeric be level_to_numeric with level as logger_level
    Let message_numeric be level_to_numeric with level as message_level
    Return message_numeric is greater than or equal to logger_numeric

Note: Create default console formatter
Process called "create_default_formatter" returns Formatter:
    Return Formatter with:
    format_template as "[{timestamp}] {level} minus {logger}: {message}"
    include_timestamp as true
    include_level as true
    include_logger as true

Note: Create console handler for stdout output
Process called "create_console_handler" returns Handler:
    Return Handler with:
    handler_type as "console"
    level as INFO
    formatter as create_default_formatter
    enabled as true

Note: Format log message using formatter
Process called "format_message" that takes formatter as Formatter and record as LogRecord returns String:
    Let formatted_message be formatter.format_template If formatter.include_timestamp:
    Let timestamp_str be format_timestamp with timestamp as record.timestamp
    Set formatted_message to replace formatted_message where "{timestamp}" becomes timestamp_str If formatter.include_level:
    Let level_str be level_to_string with level as record.level
    Set formatted_message to replace formatted_message where "{level}" becomes level_str If formatter.include_logger:
    Set formatted_message to replace formatted_message where "{logger}" becomes record.logger_name Set formatted_message to replace formatted_message where "{message}" becomes record.message Return formatted_message

Note: Check if log record passes filter
Process called "passes_filter" that takes filter as Filter and record as LogRecord returns Boolean:
    If not filter.enabled:
    Return true Match filter.filter_type:
    When "level":
    Let min_level be filter.criteria["min_level"]
    Let record_numeric be level_to_numeric with level as record.level
    Let min_numeric be level_to_numeric with level as min_level
    Return record_numeric is greater than or equal to min_numeric
    When "logger_name":
    Let pattern be filter.criteria["pattern"]
    Return record.logger_name contains pattern
    Otherwise:
    Return true

Note: Output formatted message via handler
Process called "emit_log" that takes handler as Handler and record as LogRecord:
    If not handler.enabled:
    Return If not should_log with logger_level as handler.level and message_level as record.level:
    Return Let formatted_message be format_message with formatter as handler.formatter and record as record Match handler.handler_type:
    When "console":
    Display formatted_message
    When "file":
    Note: File output would be implemented here
    Display "FILE: " + formatted_message
    Otherwise:
    Display "UNKNOWN_HANDLER: " + formatted_message

Note: Process log record through all handlers
Process called "process_record" that takes logger as Logger and record as LogRecord:
    For each filter in logger.filters:
    If not passes_filter with filter as filter and record as record:
    Return For each handler in logger.handlers:
    emit_log with handler as handler and record as record If logger.propagate and logger.parent is not None:
    Let parent_logger be logger_registry[Optional.unwrap with optional as logger.parent]
    process_record with logger as parent_logger and record as record

Note: Create new log record
Process called "create_log_record" that takes level as LogLevel and logger_name as String and message as String returns LogRecord:
    Return LogRecord with:
    timestamp as get_current_time
    level as level
    logger_name as logger_name
    message as message
    metadata as dictionary containing
    thread_id as get_thread_id
    process_id as get_process_id

Note: Core logging function
Process called "log_message" that takes logger as Logger and level as LogLevel and message as String:
    If not logger.enabled:
    Return If not should_log with logger_level as logger.level and message_level as level:
    Return Let record be create_log_record with level as level and logger_name as logger.name and message as message
    process_record with logger as logger and record as record

Note: Get or create logger by name
Process called "get_logger" that takes name as String returns Logger:
    If logger_registry contains name:
    Return logger_registry[name] Let parent_name be find_parent_logger_name with name as name
    Let parent_logger be If parent_name is not ""
    then Optional.Some with value as parent_name
    else Optional.None Let new_logger be Logger with:
    name as name
    level as INFO
    handlers as list containing
    filters as list containing
    parent as parent_logger
    propagate as true
    enabled as true Set logger_registry[name] to new_logger
    Return new_logger

Note: Find parent logger name from hierarchical name
Process called "find_parent_logger_name" that takes name as String returns String:
    Let parts be split name by "."
    Let parts_count be length of parts If parts_count is less than or equal to 1:
    Return ""
    Let parent_parts be slice parts from 0 to parts_count - 1
    Return join parent_parts with "."

Note: Initialize root logger
Process called "initialize_root_logger" returns Logger:
    Let root_logger be Logger with:
    name as "root"
    level as INFO
    handlers as list containing create_console_handler
    filters as list containing
    parent as Optional.None
    propagate as false
    enabled as true Set logger_registry["root"] to root_logger
    Return root_logger

Note: Initialize the logging system
Let root_logger as Logger = initialize_root_logger

Note: Convenience logging functions
Process called "log_trace" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as TRACE and message as message

Process called "log_debug" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as DEBUG and message as message

Process called "log_info" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as INFO and message as message

Process called "log_warning" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as WARNING and message as message

Process called "log_error" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as ERROR and message as message

Process called "log_critical" that takes logger as Logger and message as String:
    log_message with logger as logger and level as CRITICAL and message as message